com.epoch.synthesis

Class SynthParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.epoch.synthesis.SynthParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ChemConstants, MechSynthConstants, FormatConstants, SynthConstants

    class SynthParser
extends Object
implements SynthConstants
    Parses a synthesis into stages, stores the parsed synthesis.

        Copy of original MRV as imported into Java; contains molecules and graphical objects. Apparently the operations herein cause it to become unexportable.

        All of the molecules of the original response in a single Molecule. Don't use after the synthesis has been parsed!

      • getStageForArrowPoint

        private int getStageForArrowPoint(MPoint point)
        Gets 0-based index of stage with which the arrow endpoint is associated. First checks whether the arrow endpoint coincides with an MRectangle point; if not, checks whether the arrow endpoint falls within a box physically.
        Parameters:
        point - a point in an MDocument
        Returns:
        index of stage; NOT_FOUND for not found, FOUND_IN_2 for found in more than one stage

      • extractMolecules

        private void extractMolecules(boolean emptyBoxOK)
                       throws SynthError
        Extract individual molecules from the imported molecule and place them in their stages, ensuring each atom of each molecule is inside the same box. Supergroups are contracted for purposes of determining whether or not all atoms in the group are "inside the rectangle".
        Parameters:
        emptyBoxOK - whether a box may be empty
        Throws:
        SynthError - if a molecule is found not to be entirely in a single box or if a box is impermissibly empty

      • extractRxnSelections

        private void extractRxnSelections()
                           throws SynthError
        Gets reaction numbers from the MDocument, finds corresponding reaction selections, and puts them in their correct stage.
        Throws:
        SynthError - if a textbox is found to be in two boxes, or two reaction numbers are found in a single box

      • findTargetStageIndex

        private void findTargetStageIndex()
                           throws SynthError
        Finds and sets the index of the stage containing the target of the synthesis.
        Throws:
        SynthError - if the target stage can't be found, or more than one is found.
